\title{Get Numerical Summaries of Your Rate Estimates}
\description{
After fitting a model with \code{\link{fitRateScape}} or
\code{\link{rateCategories}}, this function gives you the numbers behind
the rate-painted tree: which branches have shifted rates, how fast or slow
they are, and how confident you can be in those estimates.

For Bayesian fits, this includes posterior means, credible intervals, and
Bayes factors. For ML fits, it gives you maximum likelihood estimates,
standard errors, and BIC comparisons.
}
