\item{object}{A fitted model from \code{\link{fitRateScape}} (Bayesian) or
\code{\link{rateCategories}} (ML).}

\item{burnin_frac}{Optional additional burn-in to discard, as a fraction of
the total posterior samples (0 to 1). The standard burn-in was already
removed during fitting. Use this if you suspect the chain needed more
time to converge. Default 0.}

\item{quantiles}{Which quantiles to report for credible intervals. Default
\code{c(0.025, 0.975)} gives 95\% credible intervals. Use
\code{c(0.05, 0.95)} for 90\% intervals.}

\item{...}{Currently unused.}
}
\value{
For \strong{Bayesian fits} (\code{ratescapeFit}): a list containing:
\describe{
